						<description>Caliber: 40x46mm. 1-round tube. Single shot.					
The XM148 is a single shot grenade launcher developed by Colt as an accessory to the M16 platform during the Vietnam War. At the time it was created, the Army relied on the standalone M79 grenade launcher for squad grenadiers, forcing designated units to carry a pistol or a separate rifle for self-defense, or forego carrying a secondary weapon entirely, all of which were deemed inadequate. The XM148 was produced quickly, but problems with reliability and accidental discharges meant it was mostly abandoned in favor of the M203. The US Air Force was the sole exception, with many security units using them until the end of the 20th century; some XM148s were also adapted to Australian L1A1 and L34A1 weapons for field use.</description>
